<br>
A few notes from my experience.<br>
- He is a major irritant, no matter how green he is. Killed me dead at 54 or 55.<br>
- He summons, even though he's level 35, so if you get into it with him and decide you chose poorly, you're likely dead.<br>
- I don't seem to have any trouble pulling his little alien buddies out of the room prior to engaging him. Run in, smack an alien, run out, kill it. Repeat 4 times. Makes a big difference - his friends do enough damage to be irritating, and can interrupt casting often.<br>
- First few times in I put on all sorts of resist gear and went 1hs to try to disrupt his casting. Don't. I didn't resist much of anything. Conclusion: just kill him before he kills you.<br>
- By now I've killed him 4 or 5 times, and seen the spell drop twice. Scribed it, never found a use for it. Woot?<br>
- You can make your life a little easier by running around behind him to fight him. He does a knockback, so if you move around behind him he slams you into the wall and you don't have to run as far to get engaged again.<br>
- I've wondered what would happen if you just stood outside his room and cast Thunder of Karana on him like a million times to try to drain him down. Would he summon even though you did no damage? Would it matter? Seems like his really nasty spell may be a proc anyway.<br>
- He often has a damage shield on, so may be worth dispelling him before going in as well.<br>
<br>
Hope this helps,<br>
